title: Grateful Dead Live at Oakland-Alameda County Coliseum on 1991-10-27
lineage: 16 bit – 48kHz DAT Master > TASCAM DA-20 (SPDIF out) -> LynxTWO-B Audio Reference Interface (SPDIF in) -> Wavelab 6.0 by Todd Evans Editing and Mastering: Jamie Waddell on the GEMS Edit Station. description:
Set 1

Sugar Magnolia-> Sugaree, Walkin' Blues, Althea, When I Paint My Masterpiece, Candyman, Cassidy, Touch Of Grey

Set 2

China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider, Samson & Delilah, Ship of Fools, Iko Iko*-> Mona*-> Jam*-> Drums-> Jam-> The Wheel-> I Need A Miracle-> Wharf Rat-> Good Lovin', E: Knockin' On Heaven's Door

*w/ Carlos Santana & Gary Duncan Quicksilver, guitars; Last "Mona": 03-25-72; Final GD Perfomance of "Mona"

reviews.review_text: How is this the first review? So, I gave the SBD of this show a listen and really liked it -- good energy all around. For me, the next logical step would be to download it, which meant AUD. This is a pretty great recording, and I don't see why more haven't taken advantage of it. I know it's been said hundreds of times, but this really is a great resource! Great show and good AUD, definitely worth the download.

Heartbreaking and beautiful This show was so comforting right after the tragedy of Bill Graham's death. I remember how hauntingly exciting it was when John Cipollina came out for the primal Mona. The concert was a true memorial to a legend. Thank you Bill.
Charles in-charge! What a great sounding show!  Brilliant work Charlie, thank you.  This one is a gem IMHO.  Love it.
Thanks to the Movie E.T. I'd like to thanks the producers of the movie E.T. as well since we are thanking people that have nothing to do with the source.  Loved the bicycle scene...
Best Aud source Great show.  Set 2 in particular.  Very good sound for Coliseum.  Young--Buick made great recordings of all 4 nights.  All available on the Archive.  Blows away the sbd's.
